  <article class="container">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-sm-9 col-md-10">
			<div class="inner">
				<div class="entry-content">
				    <p class="lead"></p>
    
  
  
  
  
                    <h3>OpenOdonto is an Electronic Patientl Record (EMR) application for Special Care Dentistry, which enables clinicians to access information they need about their patient in one place</h3>
<h4>Special Care Dentists provide dental care for people with complex health and care needs.</h4>

<p>Providing safe dental care for people with complex medical needs and disabilities is dependent on gathering and sharing information with other health and care professionals. </p>
<center><img width="100%" src="_attachment/guide1/guide1.png"></center>
<p>Special Care Dentists are frustrated by the inadequacies of current dental IT systems to provide the level of information that is required for safe and effective care. OpenOdonto was established to change this.</p>

<p>OpenOdonto is a collaborative, open source project developed with contributions from a range of hospitals, institutions, academic departments, companies and individuals. As an open source application, OpenOdonto provides a cost effective option for dental care. It cannot be sold to 3rd parties and is protected by the OpenOdonto CIC for the benefit of its users. </p>

<p>While it will be possible to download OpenOdonto and used it free of charge, we recommend that clinical installation is handled professionally through a commercial technology partner. This commercial partner will ensure that clinical data integrates with hospital workflows and PAS systems and that the connections to devices such as radiology and photography are robust.</p>

<p>
<p>It&nbsp;will run in a&nbsp;web browser to ensure that it can be accessed wherever needed. It includes a graphical user interface organised around the dental chart, which allow input of clinical data through a series of icons that relate to dental disease.</p>

<center><iframe width="640" height="360" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/179183525" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" webkitallowfullscreen=""></iframe>
<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/179183525"><font size="1"<i>OpenOdonto Prototype Video</a></i> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/user49308572">Odonto</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</font></p></center>

<h3>Safe patient care is provided by dentists who have the information they need. </h3>
<h4>OpenOdonto patient summery view</h4>

<p>OpenOdonto will give you a summary view of each patient. This allows dentists to get an overview of the systemic and dental condition of the patient and ensures allergies and risks are clearly flagged.</p>
<center><img width="100%" src="_attachment/guide2/guide2.png"></center><br>
<br>
<h4>OpenOdonto Dashboard View</h4>

<p>When you log into OpenOdonto you will see a dashboard view of your clinic to allow you to see&nbsp;patients in your clinic work list and track their progress. The dashboard will also give a messaging feature whereby patient records can be tagged with notes advising on clinical state or future actions. These messages are embedded in the patient record and support clinicians to clinician communication to ensure that patients requiring urgent attention can be flagged.</p>
<center><img width="100%" src="_attachment/guide4/dashboard.png"></center><br>
<br>
<h4>OpenOdonto Charting tools </h4>

<p>An example of the dental chart tool is shown below which allows the recording of dentition. These descriptions are stored as coded items which can be searched in the OpenOdonto database.</p>
<center><img width="100%" src="_attachment/guide3/guide3.png"></center>
<p>
<p>The data collected with these tools can be used to support risk assessment – for example to populate data for the RAG score.</p>
<br>
  
  
  
  
  
